		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>Feby 12&#47;66</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. I Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir and Friend&#44;</p>
				<p>I wished to see you when I was<lb/> at home on <date>Sunday</date> last&#44; but had<lb/> not the opportunity to do so.<lb/> As my preceptor and very old friend&#44; I<lb/> deem it my duty and at the  same<lb/> time a pleasure to inform you of<lb/> my engagement to <persName>miss Julia Spanier</persName><lb/> formerly of <placeName>Albany</placeName>&#44; but now of this<lb/> city &#8212; I think you are well<lb/> acquainted with the family&#44; and I trust<lb/> to have the pleasure ere long of introducing<lb/> you to the young lady I drop you<lb/> these few lines&#44; as I know they they will<lb/> give you pleasure&#44; and am as always&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Your very true friend&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">M. M. Allen</persName>&#44;</p>
				<p>&#40;Over&#41;</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>P. S. I  received this last week<lb/> <hi rend="underline">credentials</hi> for the orthodox <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> of <placeName>Fort Wayne</placeName>&#44; to represent<lb/> them in  the &#8220;Board of American Israelites&#8221;<lb/> <persName role="author">M.</persName></p>
		</body>
